WEBVTT

00:11.344 --> 00:13.930
<i>Saint? St. John?</i>

00:13.930 --> 00:18.685
Wake up, Saint!
Can I trust you?

00:18.685 --> 00:20.854
- What's going on?
- Can I trust you?

00:20.854 --> 00:22.689
- Uh, I...
- Just answer me!

00:22.689 --> 00:25.817
- ♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- You can trust me, Papa.

00:26.693 --> 00:27.986
I fucked up.

00:27.986 --> 00:33.908
I fucked up so-- so badly.

00:33.908 --> 00:35.910
- Is Mom okay?
- Listen to me.

00:35.910 --> 00:38.037
Remember, back in Mexico,
I told you I worked

00:38.037 --> 00:39.998
- for the State Department?
- Uh-huh.

00:39.998 --> 00:44.377
I was CIA. Station Chief
of the Mexico City office.

00:44.377 --> 00:47.422
- What?
- I'm a spy.

00:47.422 --> 00:52.427
A job just went FUBAR.
Top secret for the White House.

00:52.427 --> 00:56.931
- And my people got arrested.
- How could you not tell us?

00:58.516 --> 01:00.310
I need your help.

01:00.310 --> 01:03.480
Things could get hairy
for me real quick.

01:03.480 --> 01:08.109
I need you to do whatever I ask
without question.

01:08.735 --> 01:11.613
Can I trust you?

01:14.991 --> 01:18.536
Of course, Papa.

01:18.536 --> 01:20.622
Good boy.

01:22.373 --> 01:23.875
Get Windex and gloves.

01:25.084 --> 01:26.085
Okay.

01:28.421 --> 01:33.343
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:44.270 --> 01:45.480
Mm.

01:49.567 --> 01:50.860
How was work?

01:52.904 --> 01:55.406
Ooh!
<i>Comme ci, comme ça.</i>

01:56.491 --> 01:59.452
There is a chance
I will be going to prison.

02:03.540 --> 02:04.666
Wait, what?

02:05.458 --> 02:06.584
Don't worry.

02:06.584 --> 02:09.128
Go back to sleep.
Kids'll be up soon.

02:10.296 --> 02:13.216
Oh, now, where are
those little soaps I got you

02:13.216 --> 02:14.592
from the Watergate?

02:16.010 --> 02:17.637
- They may be used as evidence.
- ♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

02:17.637 --> 02:24.269
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:33.027 --> 02:34.070
Hurry!

02:50.879 --> 02:53.756
Fuck! Squat down!

02:53.756 --> 02:56.259
Make it look like
we're fixing a flat.

03:00.346 --> 03:01.472
Thank you!

03:03.224 --> 03:07.061
Get the sides, the bottom.

03:07.061 --> 03:09.856
- Wipe down everything.
- Yes, Papa!

03:09.856 --> 03:13.318
All over!
No prints. Keep rubbing.

03:13.318 --> 03:15.069
Good. Wipe it all down.

03:15.069 --> 03:17.655
- Why the typewriter?
- The less you know the better.

03:19.782 --> 03:23.161
Okay.
Grab everything. Hurry.

03:25.747 --> 03:29.042
Never tell anyone
that you did this,

03:29.042 --> 03:31.127
or we're both in big trouble.

03:37.508 --> 03:43.139
My boy. My boy, my boy.

03:49.062 --> 03:52.482
Oh. Hotel key.

03:53.608 --> 03:54.567
It's the little things.

03:54.567 --> 03:57.195
Oh, we didn't wipe that down!

03:57.195 --> 04:00.657
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:06.371 --> 04:07.705
♪ (THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

04:07.705 --> 04:10.041
♪ (MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:11.250 --> 04:13.419
Turn to your right.

04:16.673 --> 04:18.549
Turn to your right.

04:18.549 --> 04:21.302
<i>-No sé. Derecho.</i>

04:23.429 --> 04:24.472
<i>Derecha.</i>

04:35.817 --> 04:37.527
Turn to your right, please.

04:37.527 --> 04:39.112
<i>No sé, señor.</i>

04:39.988 --> 04:41.489
Turn to your right.

04:45.243 --> 04:47.662
- Do you speak English?
- Yeah.

04:47.662 --> 04:49.122
Turn to your right.

04:52.792 --> 04:54.919
<i>Gracias.</i>
- You're welcome.

04:58.631 --> 05:00.258
Fore!

05:01.342 --> 05:04.012
Goddamn it.

05:10.935 --> 05:13.479
Mr. Kleindienst?
- ♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:13.479 --> 05:14.647
Hello?

05:15.690 --> 05:18.651
I am behind
the tree to your right.

05:20.361 --> 05:21.821
My name is Gordon Liddy.

05:21.821 --> 05:24.032
I'm the Head Counsel

05:24.032 --> 05:26.868
for the Committee
to Re-Elect the President.

05:26.868 --> 05:28.786
What the hell are you doing
on my golf course?

05:28.786 --> 05:32.331
Five men were arrested
last night at the DNC.

05:32.331 --> 05:34.417
They were conducting
a clandestine intelligence

05:34.417 --> 05:36.586
- gathering operation.
- I heard.

05:36.586 --> 05:37.795
McGovern is floundering.

05:37.795 --> 05:41.257
What kind of morons
break into the goddamn DNC?

05:41.257 --> 05:43.217
Those men work for me.

05:43.217 --> 05:44.427
Oh, hell.

05:44.427 --> 05:47.013
One of the men, Jim McCord,
is Head of Security

05:47.013 --> 05:48.931
for the Committee.
Oh, fuck.

05:48.931 --> 05:50.266
Does Mitchell know?

05:50.266 --> 05:53.728
I did not take over this job
just to clean up his bullshit.

05:53.728 --> 05:55.188
Yes.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.815
In fact, Mr. Mitchell
has a request.

05:57.815 --> 06:00.693
If you could get McCord
released immediately,

06:00.693 --> 06:02.070
we would be--
On what grounds?

06:02.070 --> 06:03.237
Are you all out of your minds?

06:03.237 --> 06:04.781
Do you have any idea
what something like this

06:04.781 --> 06:06.074
could do to the president?

06:06.074 --> 06:08.868
Sir, if the world finds out
that the Head of Security

06:08.868 --> 06:12.246
for the Committee was arrested,
think about what that would do

06:12.246 --> 06:13.998
- to the president.
- Oh, Christ.

06:13.998 --> 06:15.333
McCord has fake ID.

06:15.333 --> 06:19.712
But as a former FBI agent,
he has his fingerprints on file,

06:19.712 --> 06:21.798
so it's only a matter of time
before they find out

06:21.798 --> 06:24.759
who he is and where he works.

06:24.759 --> 06:26.385
What the fuck
did you people think

06:26.385 --> 06:27.428
you were doing in there?

06:27.428 --> 06:30.932
Saving the country
from communism, sir.

06:30.932 --> 06:32.225
The clock is ticking.

06:32.225 --> 06:35.645
By my count, we have 48 hours
before they figure out

06:35.645 --> 06:38.397
- who he is.
- ♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

06:38.397 --> 06:40.358
I stake my reputation on that.

06:48.783 --> 06:50.743
Your turn.

06:50.743 --> 06:53.996
Come on. Oh, <i>sí, sí.</i>

06:53.996 --> 06:55.790
So interesting.

06:55.790 --> 06:57.667
Name?
- Eat shit.

06:57.667 --> 07:00.378
- Address?
- I wanna speak to my attorney.

07:01.003 --> 07:02.338
Phone number?

07:02.338 --> 07:05.007
I wanna speak
with my attorney.

07:05.007 --> 07:08.010
Okay, let's start
from the top. Name?

07:08.010 --> 07:12.014
Look, Mr. Martin,
I'm trying to help you out.

07:12.014 --> 07:14.392
Just tell us your real name,
or bail's gonna be

07:14.392 --> 07:16.185
100 grand at least.

07:16.185 --> 07:18.688
I want to have
an attorney present.

07:18.688 --> 07:20.314
Jim?

07:21.357 --> 07:23.401
Jimmy?

07:23.401 --> 07:25.945
- Wait, you know this guy?
- Yeah, this is Jim McCord.

07:25.945 --> 07:27.446
He does security
for John Mitchell.

07:27.446 --> 07:30.366
- No. Not anymore.
- Wow, really?

07:30.366 --> 07:31.868
- Hey there, Ted.
- Hey.

07:31.868 --> 07:34.704
Jim McCord. Thanks, Ted.

07:34.704 --> 07:35.788
Yeah, thanks, Ted.

07:35.788 --> 07:38.207
Could you spell
your last name for me?

07:38.207 --> 07:41.043
Yes, A-T-T-O-R-N-E-Y.

07:41.043 --> 07:44.046
<i>The perfect
French omelet is</i> baveuse.

07:44.046 --> 07:46.215
Now, where are the chives?

07:46.215 --> 07:50.887
We have, uh, oranges,
pickles, oyster stew, olives,

07:50.887 --> 07:51.971
no chives.

07:51.971 --> 07:53.890
When do we ever
have oyster stew?

07:53.890 --> 07:56.184
We have everything.
We have tomato juice,

07:56.184 --> 07:59.395
but we have no goddamn chives!

07:59.395 --> 08:00.897
- It's okay, Papa.
- So stupid.

08:00.897 --> 08:02.106
Don't worry about it.
I don't need...

08:02.106 --> 08:03.524
- I don't need chives.
- Okay. Fine. Fine!

08:03.524 --> 08:05.693
It'll be fine.
It's fine without the chives.

08:05.693 --> 08:06.861
It's fine. Um.

08:06.861 --> 08:08.362
Okay.
You remember, my, um,

08:08.362 --> 08:10.156
my, uh, teacher,

08:10.156 --> 08:13.201
um, at my old school,
the one who, um--

08:13.201 --> 08:14.368
Yes, I remember.

08:14.368 --> 08:17.205
Well, I told Mama about it,
and then the next day,

08:17.205 --> 08:18.539
he, uh, vanished.

08:18.539 --> 08:21.375
Your mother told me
what had happened.

08:21.375 --> 08:25.087
And that night, I threw two,
three guns into the car.

08:25.087 --> 08:28.633
And your mother got scared,
called the school to warn them,

08:28.633 --> 08:32.094
and the pervert stole off
into the night.

08:32.094 --> 08:34.138
- Were you gonna kill him?
- Kill who?

08:35.139 --> 08:36.140
What are you doing here?

08:36.140 --> 08:37.892
Why aren't you dressed
and showered?

08:37.892 --> 08:40.102
It's Saturday.
I don't go in till 3:00.

08:40.102 --> 08:41.854
Saturday.

08:41.854 --> 08:43.689
Right! Saturday.

08:43.689 --> 08:46.067
I'm gonna make you an omelet.

08:46.067 --> 08:47.818
Hunt residence.
Of course,
there's no chives.

08:47.818 --> 08:49.946
<i>Howard Hunt, please.</i>
Mm-hmm.

08:51.572 --> 08:53.741
Yep. One second. For you.

08:55.451 --> 08:56.577
Howard Hunt here.

08:56.577 --> 08:59.247
<i>This is Bob Woodward
from</i> The Washington Post.

08:59.247 --> 09:01.415
Yes. Yes, what is it?

09:01.415 --> 09:02.917
<i>I was just
kind of wondering</i>

09:02.917 --> 09:06.295
<i>why your name was on an envelope
found on one of the men arrested</i>

09:06.295 --> 09:08.714
<i>- at the Watergate?</i>
- Good God.

09:09.465 --> 09:10.758
<i>Do you care to comment?</i>

09:10.758 --> 09:13.469
In view that the matter
is under adjudication,

09:13.469 --> 09:15.471
uh, I have no comment.

09:15.471 --> 09:16.931
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:16.931 --> 09:19.684
- Wrong number.
- What? They asked for you.

09:20.726 --> 09:24.814
I'm going to be
in my office all day.

09:24.814 --> 09:26.774
Don't answer it!

09:26.774 --> 09:29.527
And if anyone comes
to the house, I'm not here.

09:31.112 --> 09:33.781
<i>Good evening.</i>

09:33.781 --> 09:36.075
<i>We have a mystery story
out of Washington.</i>

09:36.075 --> 09:38.119
<i>Five people have been arrested
and charged with breaking</i>

09:38.119 --> 09:40.746
<i>into the headquarters
of the Democratic
National Committee</i>

09:40.746 --> 09:41.831
<i>in the middle of the night.</i>

09:41.831 --> 09:43.207
<i>Among those five persons</i>

09:43.207 --> 09:45.501
<i>apprehended at the Watergate
was this man.</i>

09:45.501 --> 09:48.337
<i>James W. McCord,
a former CIA employee</i>

09:48.337 --> 09:50.923
<i>who now owns
his own private security firm.</i>

09:50.923 --> 09:52.425
<i>And guess what else he is?</i>

09:52.425 --> 09:54.468
<i>A consultant
to President Richard Nixon's</i>

09:54.468 --> 09:56.012
<i>re-election campaign committee.</i>

09:59.348 --> 10:05.438
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

10:10.026 --> 10:11.319
Gordon!

10:11.319 --> 10:12.445
Morning, Jeb.

10:12.903 --> 10:13.821
How's tricks?

10:13.821 --> 10:16.282
Gordon, this whole thing
is exploding.

10:16.282 --> 10:17.783
I'm getting calls from the FBI.

10:18.659 --> 10:19.785
Why are you shredding money?

10:19.785 --> 10:22.830
The cops found cash
with sequential serial numbers

10:22.830 --> 10:24.165
on our guys.

10:24.165 --> 10:29.295
Ergo, they can trace it
back to the bank and to us.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.380
Cuban imbeciles
were supposed to use it

10:31.380 --> 10:32.506
as bribe money.

10:32.506 --> 10:34.425
I'm sorry,
are you shredding soap?

10:34.425 --> 10:37.136
You have used up
your daily quota

10:37.136 --> 10:40.348
of moronic questions,
you towel snapper.

10:40.348 --> 10:43.184
And it is only 9:17 a.m.

10:43.184 --> 10:46.520
You're our chief counsel!
I need to know what to do here!

10:47.563 --> 10:49.607
Get the fuck out!

10:49.607 --> 10:53.027
My legal advice to you
is to hire your own attorney.

10:53.027 --> 10:56.322
Then what in the high holy fuck
are we paying you for?

10:59.784 --> 11:00.785
Jeb...

11:02.286 --> 11:03.954
I want you to know something.

11:03.954 --> 11:07.083
This maelstrom of shit
we are in right now...

11:08.501 --> 11:10.586
it's all your fault.

11:12.046 --> 11:13.422
I have to call a lawyer.

11:13.422 --> 11:15.508
Now, you're getting it, <i>Dummkopf.</i>

11:16.550 --> 11:17.718
Oh, my God.

11:22.848 --> 11:24.934
Mr. Hunt.
This is the FBI.

11:27.978 --> 11:31.065
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:32.191 --> 11:33.818
Mr. Hunt.

11:37.655 --> 11:38.739
Let's come back.

11:38.739 --> 11:42.493
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:42.493 --> 11:43.953
<i>Earlier today,</i>

11:43.953 --> 11:46.914
<i>the White House Press Secretary,
Ron Ziegler, had this to say</i>

11:46.914 --> 11:48.582
<i>about the Watergate break-in.</i>

11:48.582 --> 11:50.084
<i>My remark yesterday,</i>

11:50.084 --> 11:52.628
<i>regarding a third-rate burglary
attempt, related to the fact</i>

11:52.628 --> 11:54.755
<i>that I wasn't gonna comment
every time someone tries</i>

11:54.755 --> 11:56.841
<i>to break in somewhere,
and I'm gonna reject</i>

11:56.841 --> 11:59.760
<i>every attempt in questioning
to inject this matter</i>

11:59.760 --> 12:01.137
<i>into the White House.</i>

12:09.562 --> 12:11.564
<i>Merci.</i>

12:20.364 --> 12:21.449
<i>Bonjour, oui.</i>

12:21.449 --> 12:23.784
I'd like to place
an international call.

12:23.784 --> 12:25.870
- Mama?
- Hey, honey, it's early.

12:25.870 --> 12:28.497
Go back to sleep, okay?
Yes, I'll hold.

12:40.676 --> 12:42.219
Were you followed?

12:43.596 --> 12:44.722
Undoubtedly.

12:45.598 --> 12:46.724
But I lost them.

12:47.475 --> 12:48.517
Excellent.

12:49.185 --> 12:50.478
Nice bomb shelter.

12:50.478 --> 12:52.980
Thanks. It came with the house.
Hurry up!

13:00.905 --> 13:02.615
Did you hear
that child, Ziegler?

13:02.615 --> 13:03.949
Called it
a third-grade burglary.

13:06.076 --> 13:07.286
Right this way.

13:08.287 --> 13:10.664
FBI paid me
a little visit today.

13:10.664 --> 13:14.502
- Oh! And what did you tell them?
- Well, I didn't answer the door.

13:14.502 --> 13:18.547
I'm, uh, laying low,
playing it cool.

13:18.547 --> 13:20.883
Do not answer that!

13:20.883 --> 13:24.094
It's probably Dorothy,

13:24.094 --> 13:27.056
but I just can't bring myself
to talk with her.

13:27.056 --> 13:30.351
Good. Because your phones
are tapped by now.

13:30.351 --> 13:33.687
Bastards.
They don't tap my phone!

13:33.687 --> 13:36.899
I tap their goddamn phones!

13:38.400 --> 13:41.570
That is my <i>métier.</i> Here.

13:42.571 --> 13:43.572
Hmm.

13:46.450 --> 13:49.495
How much cash do we have left?
Zero.

13:50.788 --> 13:51.914
I shredded it.

13:52.665 --> 13:54.875
You shredded our money?

13:54.875 --> 13:58.295
The money was a direct link
to the Committee.

13:58.295 --> 14:00.089
- What else could I have done?
- Well, I don't know.

14:00.089 --> 14:05.302
Hide it, bury it, launder it.
You do not shred money!

14:05.302 --> 14:07.930
Christ!
This is all McCord's fault.

14:07.930 --> 14:09.306
Why did he leave that tape?

14:09.306 --> 14:11.642
Do not panic.

14:11.642 --> 14:13.936
We will figure this out.

14:13.936 --> 14:17.398
I'm as cool as a polar bear's
privates, <i>amigo.</i>

14:17.398 --> 14:20.401
The guy shredding money
is the one who panicked.

14:24.446 --> 14:25.489
Let it ring!

14:27.825 --> 14:31.287
Did you talk to Dean?
We need more money.

14:31.287 --> 14:32.496
<i>Shall I get that?</i>

14:32.496 --> 14:36.166
- Do not pick up!
- Why are you having a freak-out?

14:36.166 --> 14:38.127
You're not strapped
for cash, are you?

14:38.127 --> 14:39.878
Not me.

14:39.878 --> 14:43.799
The Cubans.
They need to take care of us.

14:43.799 --> 14:45.968
- Um, them.
- Listen to me.

14:45.968 --> 14:47.636
Well, if you come
under pressure,

14:47.636 --> 14:49.179
you just say

14:49.179 --> 14:50.931
you worked for me.

14:50.931 --> 14:52.641
'Cause I can take
whatever these SOBs

14:52.641 --> 14:57.021
- can dish out.
- I do not work for you, Gordon.

14:57.021 --> 14:58.939
What are you gonna say?

14:58.939 --> 15:00.899
That you worked
for the White House?

15:06.488 --> 15:08.949
- They better take care of us.
- They will.

15:08.949 --> 15:11.577
Now, you and I just need
to keep our mouths shut

15:11.577 --> 15:13.287
'til after the election.

15:13.287 --> 15:15.247
Then Nixon can pardon us
without so much

15:15.247 --> 15:18.125
as a second thought
and we are home free.

15:19.168 --> 15:22.129
Nixon is a man
who values loyalty.

15:23.255 --> 15:25.424
You're goddamn right he does.

15:29.553 --> 15:32.181
Oh, uh, should I take
the bookcase, Dr. No,

15:32.181 --> 15:34.850
or is there a trap door?

15:34.850 --> 15:36.894
♪ (UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:36.894 --> 15:38.354
<i>Two former White House aides</i>

15:38.354 --> 15:40.022
<i>with electronic
receiving devices</i>

15:40.022 --> 15:41.148
<i>were in the room</i>

15:41.148 --> 15:42.900
<i>of the Watergate Hotel
on the early morning</i>

15:42.900 --> 15:46.779
<i>of June 17th,
when five men with bugging gear</i>

15:46.779 --> 15:48.947
<i>were found
in Democratic headquarters here</i>

15:48.947 --> 15:50.282
<i>in the Watergate building.</i>

15:51.909 --> 15:53.369
<i>The men are G. Gordon Liddy,</i>

15:53.369 --> 15:55.496
<i>at that time counsel
to the Finance Committee</i>

15:55.496 --> 15:56.789
<i>to Re-Elect the President.</i>

15:56.789 --> 15:59.416
<i>And E. Howard Hunt, a former
White House consultant.</i>

15:59.416 --> 16:01.752
Mrs. Hunt! Mrs. Hunt!

16:02.961 --> 16:04.505
Mrs. Hunt,
have you seen your husband?

16:04.505 --> 16:06.215
What do you know
about the break-in at the DNC?

16:06.215 --> 16:09.301
Mrs. Dorothy Hunt, Agent Dwyer,
Agent McNeil, FBI.

16:09.301 --> 16:11.637
What is happening?
Kevan,
take David inside, okay?

16:11.637 --> 16:13.180
This is
private property. Let's go.

16:13.180 --> 16:14.556
Mrs. Hunt, we'd like a word
with your husband,

16:14.556 --> 16:16.058
but we've been unable
to track him down.

16:16.058 --> 16:18.560
I'm sorry, I've been in Europe.
I haven't heard from my husband.

16:18.560 --> 16:20.813
- He could be anywhere.
- Well, if you do see him,

16:20.813 --> 16:22.272
could you please tell him
to call us?

16:22.272 --> 16:23.524
If I see him.

16:27.695 --> 16:29.363
Howard!

16:29.363 --> 16:31.115
Oh, <i>bonjour,</i> Kev!

16:31.115 --> 16:32.908
How was your month in Paris?

16:32.908 --> 16:35.744
Oh, by the way,
do not answer the phone.

16:35.744 --> 16:37.204
W-- is Papa okay?

16:37.204 --> 16:40.124
- Hey! Look who's here!
- Papa!

16:40.124 --> 16:43.210
Anyone for pancakes?
Chocolate chip!

16:43.210 --> 16:44.878
Why is the FBI here?

16:44.878 --> 16:46.922
Oh, well, they just wanted
to ask me a few questions,

16:46.922 --> 16:49.425
but I'm not feeling
terribly chatty.

16:49.425 --> 16:51.093
Of course, he's a spy.

16:51.093 --> 16:52.761
But he's not a spy!

16:54.513 --> 16:56.223
I am.

16:56.223 --> 16:59.977
No. Don't you-- You work
for the White House.

16:59.977 --> 17:02.104
Think about it, Kev.
It makes so much sense.

17:02.104 --> 17:04.440
All the lies,
all the manipulations,

17:04.440 --> 17:06.525
all the mind games. God!

17:06.525 --> 17:09.319
This entire time we believed
that he just wrote

17:09.319 --> 17:12.281
- shitty spy books.
- They're not shitty.

17:12.281 --> 17:16.160
Thank you, Saint.
That might be my best review.

17:16.160 --> 17:18.454
So, am I getting
chocolate chip pancakes?

17:18.454 --> 17:21.707
In a bit. First, I want a word
with your father.

17:25.794 --> 17:27.629
Yeah, it's a disaster.

17:27.629 --> 17:29.256
You gotta talk
to those guys in the morning.

17:29.256 --> 17:32.426
Hmm. No, uh, tell them to talk
to Haldeman about it.

17:32.426 --> 17:34.261
- I don't want that on my desk.
- Yeah.

17:35.554 --> 17:38.015
- John!
- Jesus, Gordon.

17:38.015 --> 17:41.185
Are you the action officer
in charge of damage control?

17:41.185 --> 17:43.020
- You and I--
- Don't look at me.

17:43.020 --> 17:44.730
Just look straight ahead.

17:45.773 --> 17:48.567
You and I cannot be talking, Gordon.

17:48.567 --> 17:51.987
The FBI is crawling up
our asses.

17:51.987 --> 17:54.281
I'm in contact
with Director Gray.

17:54.281 --> 17:55.783
We're on top of it.

17:55.783 --> 17:57.409
- Are you?
- Hmm.

17:57.409 --> 17:59.953
They have Felt
running the investigation.

17:59.953 --> 18:03.248
Mark Felt was
at the first Plumbers meeting.

18:03.248 --> 18:07.086
- You're joking.
- Oh, I wish I were.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.712
Please tell me
this meeting didn't take place

18:08.712 --> 18:09.922
at the White House.

18:11.131 --> 18:12.382
I wish I could.

18:14.009 --> 18:15.385
Okay, Gray's our guy.

18:15.385 --> 18:17.679
He'll ride herd on Felt
and his FBI cronies.

18:17.679 --> 18:19.932
You guys just need
to keep your mouths shut.

18:19.932 --> 18:22.518
You need to know something.

18:22.518 --> 18:25.521
The DNC break-in
is not the problem.

18:25.521 --> 18:27.439
Our infiltration
into Dan Ellsberg's

18:27.439 --> 18:30.192
psychiatrist's office
in Beverly Hills last year...

18:30.192 --> 18:32.110
Ooh, that's the problem.

18:32.110 --> 18:34.613
That order came
from inside the White House.

18:34.613 --> 18:36.782
You know what?
You didn't tell me that.

18:36.782 --> 18:38.784
Because this conversation
never happened.

18:38.784 --> 18:41.370
How does this thing
keep finding ways to get worse?

18:42.371 --> 18:43.831
Ehrlichman okayed it.

18:44.581 --> 18:46.250
And worse.

18:46.250 --> 18:47.751
Hunt and I are prepared
to take the fall,

18:47.751 --> 18:50.379
but we expect
to be taken care of,

18:50.379 --> 18:52.005
"company style."

18:52.005 --> 18:54.216
Public disavowal,
private funding.

18:54.216 --> 18:56.677
I really hope
that you understand

18:56.677 --> 18:58.595
the scope
and scale of this thing.

18:58.595 --> 19:00.264
How dangerous this could be
to the country,

19:00.264 --> 19:02.015
to the president.

19:02.015 --> 19:03.475
The Committee has a policy
that every member

19:03.475 --> 19:06.395
must cooperate fully
with the investigation.

19:06.395 --> 19:09.523
Therefore, I will be tendering
my resignation tomorrow.

19:10.274 --> 19:11.900
And if the president wants...

19:14.695 --> 19:17.865
you just tell me
what corner to stand on.

19:17.865 --> 19:21.326
You hire a sniper
and I will take the bullet.

19:21.326 --> 19:23.579
I am prepared to die
for this president.

19:24.538 --> 19:25.622
Are you?

19:26.999 --> 19:28.292
Go home, Gordon.

19:29.209 --> 19:30.419
Get some sleep.

19:31.795 --> 19:33.338
Name the time and the place.

19:34.423 --> 19:36.717
Just make sure
it's a clean head shot!

19:39.344 --> 19:40.596
Oh, I will, Gordon.

19:46.435 --> 19:49.479
What, d'you bring back
the Eiffel Tower?

19:50.856 --> 19:51.940
You've had a long flight.

19:51.940 --> 19:54.610
Uh, how about I whip you up
a few fluffy flapjacks?

19:54.610 --> 19:55.944
What's going on, Howard?

19:55.944 --> 19:58.363
We have eggs,
we have bacon, we have, uh...

19:58.363 --> 19:59.823
What have you done?

20:07.956 --> 20:10.709
♪ (UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING
OVER RADIO) ♪

20:10.709 --> 20:12.252
It wasn't my fault.

20:12.252 --> 20:16.173
I tried and tried to talk them
out of going in again,

20:16.173 --> 20:19.051
but Gordon
kept pushing and pushing,

20:19.051 --> 20:21.595
and that idiot McCord
left the tape--

20:21.595 --> 20:25.098
Our lives, Howard.
Our house, our kids.

20:25.098 --> 20:26.183
This was not the deal.

20:26.183 --> 20:28.352
It's going to be okay.
I-- I have a plan.

20:28.352 --> 20:30.479
You take that stupid
fucking apron off.

20:30.479 --> 20:31.605
I can't even look at you.

20:31.605 --> 20:35.067
Okay. We, uh, we take the kids
to Florida.

20:35.067 --> 20:37.569
We tell them we're going
to Walt Disney World.

20:37.569 --> 20:40.656
But uh, we-- we actually
fly into Miami.

20:40.656 --> 20:43.241
And there's that
abandoned air strip

20:43.241 --> 20:45.953
outside of Opa-locka,
we-- we used in '61.

20:45.953 --> 20:48.497
- Then what?
- Then, we get Somoza to send

20:48.497 --> 20:51.166
a Nicaraguan
National Guard airplane.

20:51.166 --> 20:52.417
And then what?

20:52.417 --> 20:54.044
And then I do what I do.

20:54.044 --> 20:57.547
I work
with Nicaraguan intelligence.

20:57.547 --> 21:01.385
Uh, liaise with the Company.
Uh, it'll be like Mexico.

21:01.385 --> 21:03.971
- You loved Mexico.
- Do you hear yourself, Howard?

21:03.971 --> 21:05.931
Do you hear
how insane you sound?

21:07.557 --> 21:10.227
You need a lawyer.
We need a lawyer.

21:10.227 --> 21:11.353
No!

21:11.979 --> 21:13.981
Somoza owes me big.

21:15.232 --> 21:16.900
You know what we did down there.

21:16.900 --> 21:20.195
They all owe me,
those greasy sons of bitches.

21:20.195 --> 21:23.323
- They owe me!
- If our salvation hinges

21:23.323 --> 21:26.326
on a tin-pot dictator's sense
of rectitude,

21:26.326 --> 21:29.246
we are well and truly fucked, Howard.

21:44.845 --> 21:46.221
I'll call a lawyer.

21:47.597 --> 21:48.765
Thank you.

21:52.811 --> 21:54.438
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

21:54.438 --> 21:56.273
<i>Sweetheart,
bring us some coffee</i>

21:56.273 --> 21:59.109
and some of those yummy
Stella D'Oro cookies,

21:59.776 --> 22:00.652
you-- you know?

22:00.652 --> 22:01.945
- Yes, sir.
- Thank you.

22:01.945 --> 22:04.865
Anyway, as I was saying,

22:04.865 --> 22:07.325
this has jumped
from a misdemeanor

22:07.325 --> 22:08.452
to multiple felonies.

22:08.452 --> 22:10.537
Now, unless you've got
some way of proving

22:10.537 --> 22:13.123
that the Democrats
bugged themselves...

22:13.123 --> 22:15.751
...we have a problem, Howard.

22:15.751 --> 22:17.210
You have
to understand something.

22:17.210 --> 22:21.423
I have never worked
on US soil before.

22:21.423 --> 22:23.258
When something
goes wrong overseas,

22:23.258 --> 22:26.178
they yank you out.
They protect you.

22:26.178 --> 22:28.138
What, then,
is your endgame here?

22:28.138 --> 22:31.600
I don't know.
Uh, stay out of jail?

22:31.600 --> 22:32.642
Hmm.

22:32.642 --> 22:34.895
Liddy is meeting today
with Fred LaRue,

22:34.895 --> 22:36.271
the president's lawyer.

22:36.271 --> 22:37.939
You mean,
the president's bagman.

22:37.939 --> 22:41.610
Well, I assume they will be
discussing clemency.

22:42.903 --> 22:45.655
The president
will not forget us.

22:48.283 --> 22:51.495
I'm not a betting man,
but the odds of a pardon,

22:51.495 --> 22:56.333
- uh, one in a thousand.
- What kind of deal might he get?

22:57.167 --> 23:00.712
Dot, please. I'm the client.

23:02.380 --> 23:03.799
What kind of deal can I get?

23:03.799 --> 23:06.259
With every passing day,
the deal gets worse.

23:06.259 --> 23:07.344
You play ball now,

23:07.344 --> 23:08.929
I can probably
keep you out of jail.

23:08.929 --> 23:11.973
I am not naming names.

23:11.973 --> 23:15.644
Let me be clear,
I am not naming names.

23:15.644 --> 23:20.398
- No names will be named.
- So, it's a no on the names?

23:20.398 --> 23:22.609
That doesn't leave me much
to work with.

23:22.609 --> 23:25.946
So, what, Howard?
You're just gonna go to jail?

23:25.946 --> 23:27.197
That's your plan?

23:28.740 --> 23:30.117
- Well, no, that-- that's--
- No!

23:30.117 --> 23:31.993
It's absolutely unacceptable.

23:31.993 --> 23:35.038
I assume you're in communication
with the White House lawyers.

23:35.038 --> 23:36.790
- Now, hold on. Ma'am--
- You give them a message

23:36.790 --> 23:38.458
from Howard.

23:38.458 --> 23:40.335
You tell them
loyalty is a two-way street.

23:40.335 --> 23:42.796
I know how this game is played,
and those spineless,

23:42.796 --> 23:45.674
two-faced politicians
need to hear it.

23:45.674 --> 23:47.300
Dot, please, you can't just--

23:47.300 --> 23:50.595
I was on the last train
out of Shanghai in '49

23:50.595 --> 23:53.473
with a .25 caliber
strapped to my thigh,

23:53.473 --> 23:54.891
dressed as a peasant.

23:56.351 --> 23:59.146
If we're taking the fall,
we're not going down alone.

23:59.771 --> 24:00.981
You tell them.

24:00.981 --> 24:03.150
- Understand?
- Yes, ma'am.

24:04.109 --> 24:05.485
Let's go, Howard.

24:07.237 --> 24:08.655
I better go.

24:08.655 --> 24:10.866
- We're looking for 2500.
- ♪ (UPBEAT POP SONG PLAYING
OVER RADIO) ♪

24:10.866 --> 24:13.493
That's 2117,
so a little farther. Keep going.

24:13.493 --> 24:15.745
Why doesn't he wanna
just meet you at his office?

24:15.745 --> 24:18.623
LaRue cannot be seen with me.
Nobody can.

24:18.623 --> 24:20.250
That's why I'm taking
the service elevator

24:20.250 --> 24:21.376
up to his apartment.

24:21.376 --> 24:23.211
And Howard thinks
this a good idea?

24:23.211 --> 24:25.839
He does. Unless Dorothy
convinced him otherwise.

24:25.839 --> 24:27.591
I would never ask you
about your work.

24:27.591 --> 24:29.759
I'm only driving
because you asked me to.

24:33.555 --> 24:35.098
I have it all under control.

24:35.098 --> 24:37.851
Blame the whole break-in
on the CIA.

24:37.851 --> 24:39.978
And then they will deny it.

24:39.978 --> 24:41.271
But no one's going
to believe them

24:41.271 --> 24:43.023
because they're a bunch
of double-dealing

24:43.023 --> 24:44.274
panty-sniffers.

24:44.274 --> 24:47.277
And Dean will tell the FBI
to stop the investigation

24:47.277 --> 24:49.487
because it compromises
national intelligence.

24:49.487 --> 24:53.658
It's just really as simple--
Oh, fuck!

24:53.658 --> 24:57.037
What is it, Gordon?

24:57.037 --> 24:58.705
The president's
lawyer's apartment is

24:58.705 --> 25:01.208
at the Watergate.
Oh, that is perfect.

25:01.208 --> 25:03.710
- Should we go home?
- Oh, no. Proceed as planned.

25:03.710 --> 25:06.254
- Just take a left here.
- Roger that.

25:06.254 --> 25:08.673
Turn signals, turn signals. Sorry.

25:11.551 --> 25:13.428
Don't forget I have
a roast in the oven.

25:15.180 --> 25:17.057
I'm reporting
from Witches Island...

25:17.057 --> 25:20.101
Mr. Bittman?

25:20.101 --> 25:21.937
Good morning.

25:21.937 --> 25:24.272
Good morning.

25:24.272 --> 25:25.982
Morning.

25:25.982 --> 25:28.401
So I spoke with the prosecutor
who said he is willing, uh...

25:28.401 --> 25:30.237
♪ ("CAMELOT" BY RICHARD BURTON
PLAYING OVER STEREO) ♪

25:30.237 --> 25:32.864
- ...to discuss the...
- I am not naming names.

25:32.864 --> 25:36.326
- Yeah, I know!
- I say, I am not naming names!

25:36.326 --> 25:39.829
- We can't hear a word, Howard!
- The house is bugged!

25:39.829 --> 25:44.000
Anything we say is protected
under attorney-client privilege!

25:44.000 --> 25:45.126
What?

25:45.126 --> 25:47.671
As long as he's here,
they can't use anything!

25:47.671 --> 25:50.840
- I...
- <i>♪ The winter is forbidden
'til December ♪</i>

25:50.840 --> 25:51.967
I know.

25:51.967 --> 25:54.052
<i>♪ And exits March
The second on the dot ♪</i>

25:54.052 --> 25:55.345
You hear that, Felt?

25:56.554 --> 25:58.181
I'm not naming names!

26:00.141 --> 26:03.812
I, uh, I did come
with a spot of good news.

26:03.812 --> 26:05.313
Hmm.

26:05.313 --> 26:07.232
A guardian angel
of yours sent me

26:07.232 --> 26:09.484
25,000 dollars in cash.

26:09.484 --> 26:13.697
See? They do fear me.
How soon can we get that?

26:13.697 --> 26:14.906
Oh, you can't.

26:14.906 --> 26:17.284
Uh, but my fees are covered
for the time being

26:17.284 --> 26:19.244
so that should be something
of a relief.

26:19.244 --> 26:20.829
Now, right after
the cash arrived,

26:20.829 --> 26:25.458
I got a call from a Mr. Rivers,
who said he wanted to talk.

26:25.458 --> 26:28.378
Okay, I'll need a secure phone.

26:28.378 --> 26:31.798
Could you get our guest
some cookies or something?

26:31.798 --> 26:33.842
Well,
he didn't wanna talk to you.

26:33.842 --> 26:35.760
His exact words were,
"I wanna talk

26:35.760 --> 26:36.970
to the writer's wife."

26:39.347 --> 26:40.682
- Me?
- Her?

26:40.682 --> 26:41.808
Mm.

26:45.103 --> 26:46.604
I'm gonna need a secure phone.

26:46.604 --> 26:47.731
Yes, of course.

26:47.731 --> 26:50.233
Now, Howard,
did you say something

26:50.233 --> 26:51.860
about cookies?

26:57.240 --> 26:58.450
They're in the cupboard, dear.

27:00.744 --> 27:03.038
- Is chocolate chip okay?
- Yeah.

27:03.038 --> 27:04.205
Chocolate chip, Howard.

27:04.914 --> 27:06.124
Yes, dear.

27:08.501 --> 27:10.754
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:10.754 --> 27:13.214
This is Howard Hunt.
What should I--

27:13.214 --> 27:16.593
<i>Put your wife on the phone,
and wait in the car, Mr. Hunt.</i>

27:19.512 --> 27:20.555
It's for you.

27:22.849 --> 27:24.225
Mr. Rivers?
<i>Yes.</i>

27:24.225 --> 27:26.895
<i>Your husband's continued loyalty
to his country is appreciated.</i>

27:26.895 --> 27:29.647
<i>I'll send further instructions
through Bittman. Stay tuned.</i>

27:29.647 --> 27:30.899
And what
about the others?

27:30.899 --> 27:33.151
The Cubans, Gordon Liddy?
<i>Cubans?</i>

27:33.151 --> 27:36.196
<i>They'll be looked after.
Liddy, he's on his own.</i>

27:36.196 --> 27:37.864
Just so we're clear, Mr. Rivers,

27:37.864 --> 27:41.576
25,000 dollars is not going
to cut the mustard.

27:41.576 --> 27:43.036
It's chicken feed.

27:43.036 --> 27:45.038
<i>I understand.
Just be patient.</i>

27:45.038 --> 27:48.041
My husband and I
are as short on patience

27:48.041 --> 27:51.753
as we are on money.
Pass that along, Mr. Rivers.

27:51.753 --> 27:52.921
Good day.

27:54.422 --> 27:56.925
They wanted me
to tell you how much

27:56.925 --> 27:59.135
they appreciated your loyalty.

27:59.135 --> 28:00.595
How gratifying.

28:03.014 --> 28:05.141
There is going
to be nothing for Gordon.

28:07.769 --> 28:12.065
Sons of bitches.

28:13.483 --> 28:16.027
We'll have to take care of him.

28:17.737 --> 28:21.699
- How? Out of our end?
- He's my partner.

28:21.699 --> 28:23.034
Believe me. I know.

28:23.034 --> 28:25.745
And we can't let him know
that it's coming out of our cut

28:25.745 --> 28:28.123
or he won't take it.

28:28.123 --> 28:30.208
First things first,
how do we spread

28:30.208 --> 28:32.419
the money around?

28:32.419 --> 28:35.797
Gordon and I are both
under investigation.

28:35.797 --> 28:37.382
I suppose I can handle that too.

