31:41.149 --> 31:42.358
Get in the back.

31:42.358 --> 31:43.943
Can we get ice cream now?

31:44.611 --> 31:45.778
Of course! Let's go.

31:45.778 --> 31:47.530
What did you just take
from under the phone?

31:47.530 --> 31:48.489
Nothing.

31:48.489 --> 31:50.241
Did you just use
the fun family outing

31:50.241 --> 31:51.909
to cover up
some weird spy shit?

31:51.909 --> 31:53.828
Absolutely not.
Let's go, Howard.

31:53.828 --> 31:56.623
- Bullshit! Bullshit!
- Lisa! Enough.

31:56.623 --> 31:59.626
Oh, okay, what are you gonna do,
Mr. CIA?

31:59.626 --> 32:01.878
You're gonna send me back
to the insane asylum?

32:01.878 --> 32:04.589
This family is living
a charade of lies!

32:04.589 --> 32:06.382
I said enough!

32:06.382 --> 32:08.176
♪ ("THAT'S LIFE"
BY JAMES BROWN) ♪

32:08.176 --> 32:09.552
<i>♪ That's life ♪</i>

32:12.055 --> 32:14.182
<i>♪ That's what the people say ♪</i>

32:15.892 --> 32:17.185
This is all there was.

32:18.061 --> 32:19.646
Goddamn it.

32:19.646 --> 32:23.691
After Bittman,
we are left with only 5,000.

32:23.691 --> 32:25.151
Don't forget the Liddys.

32:25.151 --> 32:27.236
<i>♪ I'm gonna change that, too ♪</i>

32:29.155 --> 32:33.660
<i>♪ When I'm back on top in June ♪</i>

32:35.453 --> 32:38.831
<i>♪ Say that's life ♪</i>

32:38.831 --> 32:41.000
Oh, Mr. Hunt, you must know,
the tennis courts are privileges

32:41.000 --> 32:42.543
- for people...
- Don, listen to me. I-- I--

32:42.543 --> 32:44.379
- ...who have paid their dues.
- I tried to send you a check.

32:44.379 --> 32:46.172
- You have to leave, sir.
- And someone didn't mail it!

32:46.172 --> 32:47.757
Six months in a row,
someone has forgotten

32:47.757 --> 32:49.133
to mail your checks, sir.

32:49.133 --> 32:50.927
You are embarrassing me
in front of everyone!

32:50.927 --> 32:52.553
I'm sorry
I have to do this, sir.

32:52.553 --> 32:53.888
But this is my job.

32:53.888 --> 32:56.349
<i>♪ Go down
To the neighborhood bar ♪</i>

32:56.933 --> 32:58.309
It's not fair, Don.

32:59.185 --> 33:00.645
It's not fair.

33:00.645 --> 33:03.022
♪ ("DREAM A LITTLE DREAM
OF ME" BY THE MAMAS
& THE PAPAS PLAYING) ♪

33:03.022 --> 33:05.608
How's the soup, Jim?

33:06.943 --> 33:07.985
Substandard.

33:10.780 --> 33:14.242
Basically, hot tomato juice.
Might even be ketchup.

33:14.242 --> 33:16.577
The payments have stopped.
I'm sorry.

33:17.954 --> 33:19.664
Well, it's not surprising.

33:19.664 --> 33:21.708
The money's
the most incriminating thing.

33:21.708 --> 33:24.293
I can't believe Mitchell
would just abandon you.

33:24.293 --> 33:26.671
- He seemed so--
- What? Loyal?

33:26.671 --> 33:29.090
Hmm. Well, he had
the Plumbers hire you

33:29.090 --> 33:31.718
- after his wife, you know?
- After Martha had me fired?

33:31.718 --> 33:33.970
Yeah. He didn't do it
out of loyalty.

33:35.471 --> 33:37.473
He was afraid of what I know
about his family.

33:37.473 --> 33:40.184
That's all
that motivates these people.

33:40.184 --> 33:42.854
Fear and power.
Mainly the fear of losing power.

33:42.854 --> 33:44.480
But we're so close
to the election.

33:44.480 --> 33:46.983
You have to understand
something, Dorothy.

33:46.983 --> 33:50.862
These people we work for,
their cause is righteous,

33:50.862 --> 33:52.196
but their souls are...

33:53.322 --> 33:55.533
- rotten.
- Then why get involved?

33:55.533 --> 33:57.744
The same as Howard. It's a job.

34:00.955 --> 34:01.956
It's...

34:02.915 --> 34:05.126
it's not a job to him.
This, uh...

34:06.169 --> 34:08.796
war against the Left.

34:10.882 --> 34:12.049
It's like a religion.

34:13.009 --> 34:15.011
Hmm.

34:17.472 --> 34:18.639
Thanks for the soup.

34:18.639 --> 34:20.516
<i>The Democratic bugging case</i>

34:20.516 --> 34:22.101
<i>is now in the courts.</i>

34:22.101 --> 34:24.687
<i>But Mr. Nixon
and his political operatives</i>

34:24.687 --> 34:27.482
<i>have done
what no Democrat could do.</i>

34:27.482 --> 34:31.486
<i>Through their evasiveness
and their delaying tactics,</i>

34:31.486 --> 34:34.906
<i>they have made this case
of political espionage</i>

34:34.906 --> 34:39.160
<i>a major issue in this important
presidential campaign.</i>

34:39.160 --> 34:41.370
Are you ready
for the arraignment?

34:41.370 --> 34:44.332
Can anyone ever be ready
for an arraignment?

34:44.332 --> 34:45.500
That's fair.

34:46.542 --> 34:47.585
Got...

34:48.586 --> 34:50.463
fired by Mullen this week.

34:52.715 --> 34:53.841
Cowards.

34:53.841 --> 34:57.929
My boss's son
works at the DNC.

34:57.929 --> 35:00.056
McCord tapped his phone.

35:02.433 --> 35:05.603
- It's not funny.
- Come on!

35:09.482 --> 35:13.110
Dinner's served!
Look at that!

35:13.110 --> 35:15.488
- Oh, lovely...
- You are in for a treat!

35:15.488 --> 35:19.200
How about a toast
to better days?

35:19.200 --> 35:20.535
To better days.

35:22.328 --> 35:23.371
<i>Prost!</i>

35:23.371 --> 35:26.165
So, now, we just wait
for Nixon to get re-elected.

35:26.165 --> 35:27.458
Fingers crossed.

35:27.458 --> 35:29.627
Well, e-- even then...

35:30.670 --> 35:31.838
What are you trying
to say there, Dot?

35:31.838 --> 35:33.047
Well--
She's-- No. Nothing.

35:33.047 --> 35:35.341
She's not trying
to say anything.

35:35.341 --> 35:39.387
No. I-- I was just saying,
even if Nixon wins,

35:39.387 --> 35:42.723
there's no guarantees
that you all get pardons.

35:42.723 --> 35:43.933
Right, Howard?

35:45.268 --> 35:46.394
Go on, honey.

35:46.394 --> 35:48.688
Tell them your idea.

35:48.688 --> 35:50.565
Well, there--
there's plenty of time

35:50.565 --> 35:52.441
for that after dinner.
Few more drinks.

35:52.441 --> 35:54.610
- Tell them, dear.
- Here's the thing.

35:54.610 --> 35:57.488
Uh, no matter what we say
or don't say,

35:57.488 --> 35:59.532
the story is going to come out.

35:59.532 --> 36:04.996
So, why don't we tell our side
and, uh, and make

36:04.996 --> 36:07.415
- a tidy profit doing it?
- Tell them how much.

36:07.415 --> 36:10.084
Well, my agent thinks
there'll be a bidding war.

36:10.084 --> 36:14.088
And, uh, we're looking
at half a million dollars.

36:14.088 --> 36:16.257
- Maybe more.
- What?

36:16.257 --> 36:20.094
That much for a book?

36:20.094 --> 36:22.054
Unequivocally...

36:22.722 --> 36:23.764
no.

36:24.515 --> 36:27.727
Wait. So, just no?

36:29.812 --> 36:31.981
How the hell
are we supposed to live?

36:31.981 --> 36:34.942
Pay for lawyers,
schools, groceries?

36:34.942 --> 36:38.321
I've-- I've, uh,
I've gone back to teaching.

36:39.989 --> 36:43.284
Franny can stretch a chicken
like nobody's business.

36:43.284 --> 36:45.578
- We're fine.
- Oh, you're-- you're fine.

36:46.495 --> 36:48.414
This honor-among-thieves
nonsense

36:48.414 --> 36:49.916
all but guarantees
your reputations

36:49.916 --> 36:51.459
will be destroyed by others

36:51.459 --> 36:54.045
who have far less
to lose than you.

36:55.129 --> 36:56.380
But you're fine.

36:56.380 --> 37:02.053
Gordon, we will be laughed at
as third-rate burglars forever.

37:02.053 --> 37:05.932
Or with a flick
of my typewriter,

37:05.932 --> 37:09.560
we can restore our honor, right?

37:10.269 --> 37:11.395
Right.

37:14.523 --> 37:17.318
We were hired
to win a goddamned election,

37:17.318 --> 37:19.695
and to protect this country
from the Reds.

37:19.695 --> 37:24.200
So, please, tell me how writing
a tell-all book will do that?

37:24.200 --> 37:26.702
- Hmm?
- Gordon, just consider it.

37:27.870 --> 37:29.830
We never implicate
the president.

37:29.830 --> 37:31.832
We just tell our side.

37:31.832 --> 37:34.377
People need to understand
that we're not a bunch

37:34.377 --> 37:37.129
of incompetent boobs,
we're patriots

37:37.129 --> 37:40.132
who are acting
in the country's best interests.

37:40.132 --> 37:42.218
- A book, huh?
- A book.

37:42.218 --> 37:44.345
Like that book

37:44.345 --> 37:46.472
that you gave
that pretty stewardess

37:46.472 --> 37:48.641
on our way back
from Los Angeles?

37:51.602 --> 37:55.815
I-- I-- I don't, uh,
recall any stewardess.

37:55.815 --> 37:59.318
Well, she certainly
recalled you, Mr. Hamilton.

38:00.236 --> 38:01.654
Matter of fact,
she saw your picture

38:01.654 --> 38:02.905
in the paper. Hmm.

38:02.905 --> 38:05.116
Called the FBI.
Apparently, she received

38:05.116 --> 38:09.787
a copy of your latest pot boiler
and a nice handwritten note

38:09.787 --> 38:11.455
on White House stationery.

38:13.457 --> 38:18.713
On our children's lives,
Dorothy, I have no recollection

38:18.713 --> 38:20.381
of this alleged person.

38:20.381 --> 38:24.427
Probably just a, uh,
an admirer of my work.

38:24.427 --> 38:26.721
Mm-hmm.

38:26.721 --> 38:29.932
For those that need reminding...

38:31.142 --> 38:35.855
my loyalty's is not for sale,
and I am not the type...

38:37.023 --> 38:38.024
to talk.

38:39.400 --> 38:40.526
Don't.

38:41.527 --> 38:42.945
No need for that.

38:44.196 --> 38:46.699
You should be ashamed
of yourself.

38:46.699 --> 38:48.242
Oh for Christ's sake, Gordon!

38:48.242 --> 38:50.077
Do you two know
where your money's

38:50.077 --> 38:53.706
been coming from? Us.
Not the White House, not CREEP.

38:53.706 --> 38:56.751
From our own pockets. The Hunts!

38:56.751 --> 38:58.419
- Did you know this?
- ♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:58.419 --> 39:01.255
I can show you the ledgers,
down to the cent.

39:01.255 --> 39:02.923
Do you know
how much the White House,

39:02.923 --> 39:05.968
and your beloved Führer Nixon
put aside for you,

39:05.968 --> 39:07.928
and your five children?

39:08.512 --> 39:11.182
Zero. Nada. Nothing.

39:11.891 --> 39:13.309
And now, we are broke.

39:13.309 --> 39:14.852
Come on, Dot,
that's not necessary.

39:14.852 --> 39:16.979
Dead flat broke.
They need to know, Howard.

39:16.979 --> 39:19.523
The people we are protecting
are bad people.

39:19.523 --> 39:22.651
So let's drop
this loyalty bullshit.

39:23.986 --> 39:26.447
We are the only ones
in this whole situation...

39:27.490 --> 39:28.908
who've been looking out for you.

39:30.910 --> 39:32.828
The food
looked delicious, Fran.

39:35.790 --> 39:37.166
Goodnight, Gordon.

39:39.877 --> 39:41.003
I'm so sorry.

39:41.003 --> 39:43.255
Sit down, Francis.
It's dinner time.

39:46.258 --> 39:47.551
And never apologize.

39:48.552 --> 39:50.805
- Makes us look weak.
- Right.

39:50.805 --> 39:54.475
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

39:54.475 --> 39:56.644
<i>Order, order.</i>

39:56.644 --> 39:58.813
Pre-preliminary hearing
to be set

39:58.813 --> 40:01.148
within ten court days.
Thank you.

40:03.192 --> 40:06.320
Charges are,
one count of conspiracy,

40:06.320 --> 40:08.864
two counts of burglary
and three counts

40:08.864 --> 40:11.033
of eavesdropping.

40:11.033 --> 40:13.494
Would anyone care
to be heard on bail?

40:13.494 --> 40:14.954
No, your honor.

40:14.954 --> 40:16.664
Bail is set at 10,000 dollars.

40:16.664 --> 40:18.958
Gordon.

40:18.958 --> 40:21.794
Gordon.

40:27.758 --> 40:30.302
Pay the clerk the ten percent
and you can go.

40:30.302 --> 40:32.012
Blood from a stone.

40:33.013 --> 40:34.181
Don't leave town.

40:41.981 --> 40:43.190
Goes for you, too.

40:43.899 --> 40:45.526
Oh, I'm not going anywhere.

40:46.652 --> 40:49.113
My bail bondsman
is also my mother.

40:49.113 --> 40:50.656
Pay the man, Mother.

41:00.583 --> 41:02.877
Gordon, can we talk?
Come on.

41:13.471 --> 41:16.640
Oh, Gordon! Gordon!

41:16.640 --> 41:18.392
Would you care
to make a comment?

41:18.392 --> 41:19.810
How is everybody doing today?

41:23.189 --> 41:24.607
Mr. Hunt! Mr. Hunt!

41:24.607 --> 41:26.609
Howard, how does it feel to be
called a third-rate burglar

41:26.609 --> 41:28.527
- by the White House?
- Mr. Hunt!

41:28.527 --> 41:30.696
Come on, any comment?
Any comment at all?

41:30.696 --> 41:32.072
Would you like
to make a comment for...

41:32.072 --> 41:34.575
What part of no comment
don't you understand!

41:34.575 --> 41:35.784
Now, scram!

41:35.784 --> 41:38.370
Pass on another message
to the White House.

41:38.370 --> 41:41.332
Politely remind them
about what I have

41:41.332 --> 41:43.500
in my safe on Fielding.

41:43.500 --> 41:46.337
And if they don't come through
with more money,

41:46.337 --> 41:48.714
I'm going to blow them
out of the water.

41:48.714 --> 41:52.384
I know things
about presidents past,

41:52.384 --> 41:55.596
and present,
and a little event in Dallas

41:55.596 --> 41:57.514
that could tear
this country apart.

41:57.514 --> 42:01.435
I'll-- I'll pass it on.

42:09.443 --> 42:11.403
Mama, are we in trouble?

42:11.403 --> 42:12.571
You?

42:12.571 --> 42:14.949
No. Why-- Why would you
be in trouble?

42:16.659 --> 42:17.993
What about Papa?

42:19.828 --> 42:20.829
I don't know.

42:23.082 --> 42:27.002
I am so sorry.
This is all my fault.

42:27.002 --> 42:29.922
You're all paying
for my mistakes.

42:29.922 --> 42:32.424
- No.
- I should have put my foot down.

42:33.634 --> 42:35.928
- I know better. And now--
- It's not your fault.

42:37.137 --> 42:39.515
You know, I came back
from Paris to leave him.

42:40.474 --> 42:42.393
I've tried to leave him
so many times.

42:42.393 --> 42:44.645
And then the accident,
I-- I didn't think Lisa

42:44.645 --> 42:47.356
could handle the divorce.
I'm so dumb.

42:47.356 --> 42:49.984
Mama, it's okay.

42:49.984 --> 42:53.237
- You kept the family together.
- And here we are.

42:54.738 --> 42:57.616
I know how seductive
Papa can be.

42:58.826 --> 43:00.995
What's
that supposed to mean?

43:00.995 --> 43:02.413
Oh, no-- nothing.
Then what?

43:02.413 --> 43:04.123
What-- What are you
talking about?

43:04.123 --> 43:06.458
We just, um,
did some stuff together.

43:06.458 --> 43:07.626
What stuff?

43:08.794 --> 43:12.840
Um... I, uh, you know?
Nothing, really.

43:12.840 --> 43:14.967
I just helped him, you know...

43:16.010 --> 43:19.346
clean-- clean some equipment.
And, uh...

43:19.346 --> 43:21.765
it-- it was microphones
and-- and, uh,

43:21.765 --> 43:22.975
tape-- tape recorders.

43:22.975 --> 43:26.395
And, um, it was the morning
after the arrests.

43:26.395 --> 43:30.399
Oh, my God.
He had you destroy evidence?

43:30.399 --> 43:32.651
I don't know.
It was his typewriter,

43:32.651 --> 43:33.777
and...
Mm-hmm.

43:33.777 --> 43:37.948
Um, I-- We just threw it
all into the river.

43:37.948 --> 43:41.285
Thank you for-- for telling me.

43:41.285 --> 43:43.746
You know,
it's actually kind of far out.

43:43.746 --> 43:48.417
We've been getting along
a lot better lately.

43:48.417 --> 43:51.628
Well, your father is always
at his best when it's too late.

43:58.218 --> 43:59.678
Go.

44:01.347 --> 44:02.765
Here.

44:06.185 --> 44:08.312
Make sure
they give him fresh carrots.

44:09.355 --> 44:10.647
He knows
when they're fresh, okay?

44:10.647 --> 44:14.735
Will do, Mrs. Hunt. Don't worry.
They've got a fine new home.

44:14.735 --> 44:16.487
<i>Reporting from</i> CBS News'

44:16.487 --> 44:17.821
<i>election headquarters
in New York.</i>

44:17.821 --> 44:19.782
<i>Here is correspondent
Walter Cronkite.</i>

44:19.782 --> 44:21.658
<i>We can now say on the basis</i>

44:21.658 --> 44:24.203
<i>of our sample precincts
from South Dakota</i>

44:24.203 --> 44:27.289
<i>that Senator McGovern
has not won his home state.</i>

44:27.289 --> 44:29.166
<i>But President Nixon will win...</i>

44:29.166 --> 44:30.918
This-- This gives me hope!
<i>- ...South Dakota</i>

44:30.918 --> 44:34.755
<i>when all the votes are in
by 55 to 45 percent.</i>

44:34.755 --> 44:37.925
Whatever trials and tribulations
I have been through...

44:39.009 --> 44:39.885
it was worth it.

44:39.885 --> 44:41.512
Have you met
the president yet, Dad?

44:41.512 --> 44:44.390
No, Son. But the president
once gave a memo

44:44.390 --> 44:47.226
- I wrote an A-plus.
- What kind of memo?

44:47.226 --> 44:50.687
Well, I suggested
he replace J. Edgar Hoover

44:50.687 --> 44:51.897
as head of the FBI.

44:51.897 --> 44:54.400
And I felt that Hoover
was lacking judgment,

44:54.400 --> 44:55.984
and I questioned his loyalty.

44:55.984 --> 44:59.405
The president called it
the best memo he'd ever read.

44:59.405 --> 45:02.116
- Wow.
- Goddamn.

45:02.116 --> 45:03.701
That was a hell of a memo.

45:05.411 --> 45:06.495
Oh, goddamn it!

45:06.495 --> 45:08.080
<i>And there's the senator</i>

45:08.080 --> 45:09.915
<i>approaching the podium.</i>

45:09.915 --> 45:12.251
<i>Senator McGovern's speech
tonight will most certainly be</i>

45:12.251 --> 45:13.544
<i>the most effective</i>

45:13.544 --> 45:15.879
<i>- of his whole campaign.</i>
- Oh, real effective, dummy.

45:18.507 --> 45:19.842
Who did you vote for?

45:20.968 --> 45:22.928
None of your business.

45:22.928 --> 45:25.514
We need the president to win
so that he can pardon Papa.

45:25.514 --> 45:27.516
- What's a pardon?
- Nothing.

45:27.516 --> 45:30.352
<i>And 496 electoral votes</i>

45:30.352 --> 45:32.896
<i>in comparison
to McGovern's two states</i>

45:32.896 --> 45:36.817
<i>- resulting in 17...</i>
- Well, it was all for nothing.

45:38.026 --> 45:40.028
- Come on, Dot.
- Hmm.

45:40.028 --> 45:43.198
All of your Watergate...

45:45.534 --> 45:46.702
was for nothing.

45:46.702 --> 45:51.039
What are you talking about?
This-- Th...

45:52.666 --> 45:56.128
...is a victory
for America...

45:56.128 --> 45:59.173
- Mm-hmm.
- ...for democracy, for freedom,

45:59.173 --> 46:03.343
for law and order
and we are on the winning side.

46:03.343 --> 46:07.347
- Now, Nixon can do it.
- Oh, my God, Howard, wake up!

46:07.347 --> 46:09.391
Nixon isn't going
to do anything,

46:09.391 --> 46:11.810
because now,
he doesn't fucking have to.

46:11.810 --> 46:14.563
And our whole world is broken.

46:14.563 --> 46:16.398
Just like
your stupid typewriter.

46:18.859 --> 46:21.570
- Honey, trust me, Nixon--
- Oh, fuck Nixon!

46:21.570 --> 46:27.159
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

46:27.159 --> 46:30.788
- Your mother didn't mean that.
- Sounded like she meant it.

46:39.213 --> 46:43.133
Fresh cash is a hopeful sign.
It means they care.

46:43.133 --> 46:44.551
Sure.

46:44.551 --> 46:46.887
Are you nervous about the trip?

46:46.887 --> 46:48.931
It's just a quick stop
in Chicago--

46:48.931 --> 46:50.933
Howard, when I get back
I'm taking David,

46:50.933 --> 46:53.310
and we're leaving.
I want a divorce.

46:57.064 --> 46:59.066
Listen, I know-- I know
I've made mistakes--

46:59.066 --> 47:00.609
Save it, Howard.

47:01.568 --> 47:03.111
Dorothy, please, I...

47:04.863 --> 47:08.283
You know, there's something
I never told you.

47:08.283 --> 47:12.287
Back when we first got together,
my station chief pulled me

47:12.287 --> 47:15.290
into his office
and showed me a file.

47:15.290 --> 47:16.458
